This paper deals with secure communication in the presence of an eavesdropper, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves network coding and index coding, which are related to network information theory (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the equivalence between different setups, which could be considered as a theoretical computer science topic (cs.CC).
